description: Teqnion AB markets and sells components, machines, systems, and services. The company is headquartered in Solna, Stockholm and currently employs 278 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2019-04-04. The Group aims to acquire niche companies with the goal to create growth in selected product areas and markets with a limited business risk. The acquired companies continue to act and operate independently. All subsidiaries operate within narrow technology niches for the industry in the Nordic region, within industries such as laboratory equipment, electricity, design and workshop.
naics: Navigational, Measuring, Electromedical, and Control Instruments Manufacturing
